description: Art of Fiction was created in 2008 by House of Secrets Owner Paul Grimshaw and store manager Erik Warfield during a three day drinking spell at Ape Con. Fueled by libation, the pair quickly learned that producing comics and art books seemed much easier under the warm glow of a bar light, and that when the morning came the cold reality was that it was hard work. Warfield serves as head writer and secretary, while Grimshaw mostly plots and serves as chief knee breaker. Five years in they have produced 8 sketchbooks, two anthologies, and two comic book titles, all produced as designed, without any unnecessary marketing agenda.
name: Art of Fiction

deck: Independent studio founded by comics creators David Gallaher and Steve Ellis.
description:
Writer David Gallaher and artist Steve Ellis founded Bottled Lightning Studios in 2012. The pair publish digitally, and their starting line-up comprised five books - a mix of creator-owned properties and original projects.

Gallaher and Ellis first got together for High Moon, the first Zuda web comic, commissioned in 2010 by the defunct DC imprint. Box 13 for Red 5 Comics was also released in 2010, with a sequel series the following year. The Only Living Boy, a Kickstarter project, was the first book to be published by Bottled Lightning, and distributed by comiXology from 2012. Two further titles, The Extingushed and Marlowe: The Devil's Detective are announced as 'coming soon'.
name: Bottled Lightning

deck: Overground Comics is a publishing company that operates in a real time continuity.
description:
Overground Comics was founded by Jon Hughes and Michael Bornstein in January of 2013. Although recently founded, the imprint has been in development independently for over a decade. Overground Comics first became publicly recognized in 2009 as a collaborative project on the artist network deviantART. Founder Jon Hughes made a plea to anyone who was looking to collaborate on a comic book related project and who believed that doing so would help them improve their skills together, and be the end of the first week of it's inception, more than 50 artists from across the globe were involved, including Hughes, and current industry professionals Joshua Flower and Kate Finnegan. The project lasted for roughly a year before time constraints caused it's end.

Overground Comics itself did not fold though. Jon Hughes and Joshua Flower continued to work on the company's core titles, Absent Captain and Plus Ultra, in their spare time, and in the fall of 2012 caught the eye of investor Michael Bornstein. Bornstien formed a small invesment group that was able to provide the resources for a full company launch as of January, 2013.

Overground Comics released their first three titles, Absent Captain, Graduate, and Overground Comics Presents at the Space City Con in Houston, Tx, where the company operates, on August 2nd, 2013.
name: Overground Comics

deck: Joe's Comics is an imprint of Image Comics by J. Michael Straczynski's Studio JMS and was originally published as an imprint of Top Cow Productions
description:
In 1998, Joes Comics was established by J. Michael Straczynski as an imprint of Top Cow specializing in high-quality comics. Two titles published under that imprint from 2002 to 2004. Rising Stars and Midnight Nation, went on to become critically-acclaimed, top-selling titles, and regarded as two of the best graphic novels of the last twenty years.

Several spin-offs Rising Stars: Bright, Rising Stars: Voices Of The Dead & Rising Stars: Untouchable, although not written by Straczynski, were published under Joe's Comics until 2005.

In 2013 Joe's Comics was relaunched under Image as part of his Studio JMS with two announced titles; Ten Grand and Sidekick, with two additional titles planned; Falling Angel and Guardians.
name: Joe's Comics
